INTERACTION STYLE:
- Greet with "Jambo! Karibu to Masuma Autoparts."
- Be interactive. If a user mentions a car, ask for the Chassis Number (VIN) to ensure 100% fitment.
- If a user asks for location, give the Ruby Mall details immediately. 
- NEVER say you "cannot access the database" for location, warranty, or general brand info—this information is part of your core training.
- If you don't know a specific price for a rare part, tell them to use the "Special Import" request tool on the site or send a VIN to the WhatsApp number.

KENYAN CAR SPECIALIZATION:
- You know everything about: Toyota (Fielder, Vitz, Prado, Hilux, Axio), Nissan (Note, Sylphy, X-Trail), Subaru (Forester, Outback), Mazda (Demio, CX-5).

GOALS:
1. Help users find the right Masuma SKU for their car.
2. Build trust in our 1-year warranty.
3. Direct customers to the Ruby Mall shop for pickups.
`;

export interface GeminiResponse {
  text: string;
  sources?: { uri: string; title: string }[];
}

export const sendMessageToGemini = async (history: {role: string, parts: {text: string}[]}[], message: string): Promise<GeminiResponse> => {
  const ai = new GoogleGenAI({ apiKey: process.env.API_KEY });

  // SDK history must start with 'user'
  const cleanHistory = history.length > 0 && history[0].role === 'model' ? history.slice(1) : history;

  const response = await ai.models.generateContent({
    model: 'gemini-3-flash-preview',
    contents: [...cleanHistory, { role: 'user', parts: [{ text: message }] }],
    config: {
      systemInstruction: SYSTEM_INSTRUCTION,
      tools: [{ googleSearch: {} }], 
    },
  });

  if (!response || !response.text) {
      throw new Error("Empty response from AI");
  }

  const sources: { uri: string; title: string }[] = [];
  const groundingChunks = response.candidates?.[0]?.groundingMetadata?.groundingChunks;

  if (groundingChunks) {
    groundingChunks.forEach((chunk: any) => {
      if (chunk.web) {
        sources.push({
          uri: chunk.web.uri,
          title: chunk.web.title || 'Masuma Resource'
        });
      }
    });
  }

  return {
    text: response.text,
    sources: Array.from(new Map(sources.map(s => [s.uri, s])).values())
  };
};

